</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="235" pageNumber="513" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="235.[1991,2587,1435,1858]" pageId="235" pageNumber="513">
<taxonomicName box="[1995,2207,1554,1583]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Calomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="235" pageNumber="513" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="miurus">Calomys miurus</taxonomicName>
was in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[1995,2111,1589,1622]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Calomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="235" pageNumber="514" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sorella">C. sorella</taxonomicName>
until H. Zeballos and colleagues in 2014 elevated it to a valid species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1991,2445,1707,1740]" pageId="235" pageNumber="513" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6708028" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6708028" box="[1991,2445,1707,1740]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6708028/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="235" pageNumber="513" targetBox="[1377,1968,1444,1858]" targetPageId="235">
<paragraph blockId="235.[1991,2587,1435,1858]" box="[1991,2445,1707,1740]" pageId="235" pageNumber="513">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1991,2168,1707,1740]" pageId="235" pageNumber="513">Distribution.</emphasis>
Andes in WC Peru.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="235" pageNumber="513" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="235.[1991,2587,1435,1858]" lastBlockId="235.[1378,2584,1865,2450]" pageId="235" pageNumber="513">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1992,2242,1747,1780]" pageId="235" pageNumber="513">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 69-98 mm, tail 42-80 mm, ear 13-21-3 mm, hindfoot 11-22 mm; weight 11-1-28 g. Dorsum of the Short-tailed 
<taxonomicName authority="Mouse" authorityName="Mouse" box="[1609,1807,1865,1898]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Vesper" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="235" pageNumber="513" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Vesper Mouse</taxonomicName>
is chamois to isabella (pale gray-yellow), with very few dark hairs (absent in most specimens); venteris whitish; ears are honey-yellow to chamois; hindfeet are olive-buff; and tail is bicolored, drab dorsally and olive-buff ventrally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1380,2369,1983,2016]" pageId="235" pageNumber="513" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="235.[1378,2584,1865,2450]" box="[1380,2369,1983,2016]" pageId="235" pageNumber="513">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1380,1491,1983,2016]" pageId="235" pageNumber="513">Habitat.</emphasis>
Pluvial montane subtropical forest at elevations up to 4100 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="235" pageNumber="513" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph blockId="235.[1378,2584,1865,2450]" pageId="235" pageNumber="513">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1380,1644,2023,2056]" pageId="235" pageNumber="513">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
The Short-tailed 
<taxonomicName authority="Mouse" authorityName="Mouse" box="[1897,2095,2023,2056]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Vesper" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="235" pageNumber="513" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Vesper Mouse</taxonomicName>
is omnivorous, with little seasonal dietary differences in presence or absence of arthropods, plant remains, or mycorhizal spores, but significant differences in occurrence of intact seeds.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="235" pageNumber="513" type="breeding">
<paragraph blockId="235.[1378,2584,1865,2450]" pageId="235" pageNumber="513">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1380,1514,2141,2174]" pageId="235" pageNumber="513">Breeding.</emphasis>
Lactating Short-tailed 
<taxonomicName authority="Mice" authorityName="Mice" box="[1846,2021,2141,2174]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Vesper" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="235" pageNumber="513" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Vesper Mice</taxonomicName>
were reported in May and August and pregnant females in July-August.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1378,1853,2220,2253]" pageId="235" pageNumber="513" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="235.[1378,2584,1865,2450]" box="[1378,1853,2220,2253]" pageId="235" pageNumber="513">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1378,1614,2220,2253]" pageId="235" pageNumber="513">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
